OL,6,FThe question in Holyrood is why did Ms
OL,7,FForbes, who ran Mr Yousaf extremely
OL,8,Fclose in the race to replace Nicola
OL,9,FSturgeon just over a year ago, not
OL,10,Fthrow her hat in the ring.
OL,12,FThe answer appears to lie in a mix of
OL,13,Fpragmatism and principle - as is often
OL,14,Fthe case when political decisions are
OL,15,Fmade.
OL,17,FMost observers believe that , a former
OL,18,Fparty leader, ex-deputy First
OL,19,FMinister, and party stalwart for four
OL,20,Fdecades would have been harder to beat
OL,21,Fthan Mr Yousaf nearly was.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/11
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
